Ask HN: Easy way to build a UI that I can add to a rails app?
text:
I have a rails app and I need to build a good UI for my website. It has a form and requires CRUD operations and has 3/4 pages. The backend is in place, but I'm not quite comfortable with the UI part. I need to build a UI that is responsive. Are there any recommended drap/drop UI builders that can export the required HTML/CSS that I can just shove into my existing rails app?

Sites like wordpress will allow me to create a UI and some backend but it is a new backend that I'll need to learn. I'd rather keep the backend as rails as I'm comfortable with it, so it'll be faster for me to build on it.
